Mylochromis guentheri is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is found over sandy substrates.  This species can reach a length of 20 centimetres (7.9 in) TL.  This species can also be found in the aquarium trade. The specific name honours the German-born British zoologist, ichthyologist, and herpetologist Albert GÃ¼nther (1830-1914).